goals.question: What is the distribution of job counts across different years?

goals.question: What is the percentage distribution of job types in the dataset?

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    job_counts = data.groupby('job')['count'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
    job_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Job Types')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job types in the dataset?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['count'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('How has the count of jobs changed over the years?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['job', 'sex']).sum().reset_index()
    men = data[data['sex'] == 'men']
    women = data[data['sex'] == 'women']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(men['job'], men['count'], label='Men')
    ax.bar(women['job'], women['count'], bottom=men['count'], label='Women')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_xlabel('Job')
    ax.set_title('What is the gender distribution across different job types?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['year', 'count']]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['count'], bins=50, alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Job Count')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of job counts across different years?')
    ax.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    ax.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    job_counts = data.groupby('job')['count'].sum()
    job_counts.plot(kind='pie', autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, shadow=False, legend=True)
    plt.title('What is the percentage distribution of job types in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
